<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="39140" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="39140">Description</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="39140">
Morphological characters of specimens (n = 2 males) from Son La Province agreed with the descriptions of 
<bibRefCitation author="Ohler, A" journalOrPublisher="Alytes" pageId="0" pageNumber="39140" pagination="23 - 42" refId="B5306080" refString="Ohler, A, 2003. Revision of the genus Ophryophryne Boulenger, 1903 (Megophryidae) with description of two new species. Alytes 21: 23 - 42" title="Revision of the genus Ophryophryne Boulenger, 1903 (Megophryidae) with description of two new species" volume="21" year="2003">Ohler (2003)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Hecht, V L" journalOrPublisher="Biodiversity Journal" pageId="0" pageNumber="39140" pagination="507 - 552" refId="B5305960" refString="Hecht, V L, Pham, C T, Nguyen, T T, Nguyen, T Q, Bonkowski, M, Ziegler, T, 2013. First report on the herpetofauna of Tay Yen Tu Nature Reserve, northeastern Vietnam. Biodiversity Journal 4: 507 - 552" title="First report on the herpetofauna of Tay Yen Tu Nature Reserve, northeastern Vietnam" volume="4" year="2013">Hecht et al. (2013)</bibRefCitation>
: SVL 37.2-39.0 mm; head small, wider than long (HL 10.4-10.6 mm, HW 10.8-11.0 mm, HL/SVL 27-28%, HW/SVL 28-29%); snout truncate, protruding, projecting beyond upper jaw (SL 3.9-4.1 mm), shorter than horizontal diameter of eye (EL 4.3-4.6 mm); loreal region vertical, concave; nostril lateral, closer to tip of snout than to eye (NS 1.4 mm, EN 2.0-2.3 mm); interorbital space flat, narrower than upper eyelid and internarial distance (IOD 2.4-2.6 mm, UEW 3.5-3.9 mm, IN 2.9-3.2 mm); tympanum round, distinct (TD 2.9-3.0); vomerine teeth absent; tongue round; vocal sacs present in males.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="39140">Forelimb slender (FLL 23.5-24.5 mm); relative finger lengths I &lt;II = IV &lt;III, tips of fingers round, not enlarged; fingers free of webbing; subarticular tubercles absent; palmar tubercles indistinct.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="39140">Hindlimbs slender (HLL 52.9-57.1 mm); tibia longer than thigh (TL 16.9-18.0 mm, FL 16.6-17.1 mm); relative toe lengths I &lt;II &lt;V &lt;III &lt;IV; tips of toes round, slightly swollen; webbing rudimentary; subarticular tubercles indistinct; metatarsal tubercle indistinct; tibio-tarsal articulation reaching to eye.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="39140">Skin. Dorsal surface shagreened, with symmetric glandular ridges; flanks shagreened covered with granules; ventral surface smooth.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="39140">
Colouration in life. Dorsum greyish or light brown, upper surface of limbs with transverse dark brown bars; flanks with some small black spots; ventral surface cream with dark brown marbling (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F5306242" captionText="Figure 6. Megophrys microstoma (TBU SL. 2016.419, adult male) from Son La Province, Vietnam. Photo by A. V. Pham" figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.7.e39140.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/324974" pageId="0" pageNumber="39140" tableDoi="10.3897/BDJ.7.e39140.figure6">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="39140" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="39140">Distribution</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="39140">
In Vietnam, this species has been recorded from Lao Cai and Ha Giang in the North southwards to Dak Lak and Lam Dong provinces (
<bibRefCitation author="Nguyen, S V" journalOrPublisher="Edition Chimaira, Frankfurt am Main" pageId="0" pageNumber="39140" refId="B5306039" refString="Nguyen, S V, Ho, C T, Nguyen, T Q, 2009. Herpetofauna of Vietnam. Edition Chimaira, Frankfurt am Main" title="Herpetofauna of Vietnam" year="2009">Nguyen et al. 2009</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Hecht, V L" journalOrPublisher="Biodiversity Journal" pageId="0" pageNumber="39140" pagination="507 - 552" refId="B5305960" refString="Hecht, V L, Pham, C T, Nguyen, T T, Nguyen, T Q, Bonkowski, M, Ziegler, T, 2013. First report on the herpetofauna of Tay Yen Tu Nature Reserve, northeastern Vietnam. Biodiversity Journal 4: 507 - 552" title="First report on the herpetofauna of Tay Yen Tu Nature Reserve, northeastern Vietnam" volume="4" year="2013">Hecht et al. 2013</bibRefCitation>
). Our new record in Son La Province filled the distribution gap of the species in northwestern Vietnam. Elsewhere, the species is known from China, Laos, Thailand and Cambodia (
<bibRefCitation author="Fei, L" journalOrPublisher="Science Press, Beijing" pageId="0" pageNumber="39140" refId="B5305932" refString="FrostD RAmphibian species of the worldhttp://research.amnh.org/herpetology/amphibia/index.php2019-07-30T00:00:00+03:00" year="2009">Frost 2019</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="39140" type="ecology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="39140">Ecology</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="39140">The specimens were found between 19:30 and 22:00 h on branches or stones near rocky streams. The surrounding habitat was secondary forest composed of medium hardwoods and shrubs.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
